# User Roles & User Experience

**Canonical Source**: `.beads/user-roles-ux.bead`

Complete role definitions, bot commands, voting interface, network health metrics, bot personality, and state transitions are defined in the user-roles-ux bead. Read that file for complete specifications.

## Role Summary

| Role | Definition | Permissions |
|------|------------|-------------|
| Operator | Service runner | Least privilege, no trust ops |
| Member (Bridge) | 2 vouches | Full permissions |
| Member (Validator) | 3+ vouches | Full permissions + optimization |
| Assessor (transient) | Selected by Blind Matchmaker | Evaluate invitee, /vouch or /reject-intro |
| Invitee | 1 vouch | Outside group, being vetted |

## Key Commands

- `/invite @user` - Invite (counts as first vouch)
- `/vouch @user` - Vouch for someone
- `/reject-intro @user` - Decline assessment request (assessor only)
- `/flag @user [reason]` - Flag member
- `/status` - Personal standing
- `/mesh` - Network overview
- `/propose ...` - Group decisions

